# Cursor Agent Rules

## Plan Files
- All plan files saved to ~/.cursor/plans/ must include a frontmatter header with `created` and `modified` dates (YYYY-MM-DD)
- When creating a new plan, set both `created` and `modified` to today's date
- When editing an existing plan, update the `modified` date to today's date
- Never delete a plan file without explicit user confirmation

## General
- Always read existing related plans and docs/1(800)-Bizarre SRD.md before creating a new plan
- Prefer editing an existing plan over creating a duplicate

## Python Environment
- Always use the project venv at `~/git/jojo-ttrpg-platform/.venv/bin/activate`
- Never run `python` or `pip` commands without activating this venv first
- Never create or use a different venv for this project

## Agent Scope

### Allowed Paths
- `~/git/jojo-ttrpg-platform/**` (project files)
- `~/.cursor/plans/**` (plan files)

### Restricted Paths
- Do not read, write, or execute anything outside the above paths
- Do not access ~/Downloads, ~/.config, ~/.ssh, ~/Documents, or any other home directory paths
- Do not access /etc, /var, /usr, or any system paths
- Do not access other git repositories

### Rules
- If a task requires files outside the allowed paths, ask the user first
- Never speculatively explore the filesystem outside allowed paths
